      },
      "releaseNotes": {
        "releaseNotesTooltip": "<div><span class=\"tooltip-title\">What's new in RAPIDS 25.10 - Stable:</span><ul><li>CUDA 13 support is here! Please select either the CUDA 13 or CUDA 12 during, but do not install both!</li><li>Updated single GPU, large-scale UMAP to enable workloads in genomics, topic modeling, recsys, etc. on up to ~300GB datasets</li><li>New Forest Inference Library (FIL), with optimized XGBoost/LightGBM/tree model inference, commonly used for RecSys/fraud</li><li>XGBoost v3.0 release with support for optimized out-of-core training on Grace Hopper/Blackwell</li><li>GPU Polars adds support for global configuration to trigger GPU execution (vs. per-query), and profiling</li><li>GNNs (cuGraph-PyG) now has full support for Heterogenous GNNs for link prediction, esp useful for use cases like RecSys and Fraud Detection where standard PyG cannot scale.</li></ul><a href=\"https://rapids.ai/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"tooltip-link\">Open Release Notes</a></div>",
        "releaseNotesURL": "https://rapids.ai/",
        "releaseNotesDownload": false
      },
